Note:
Erlang Translation Round-Trip Probe

End-to-end proof that the Erlang translation pipeline is REAL, not a skeleton:

    Erlang source
      -> erlang_lexer      (tokenize: -module/-export/-record/-type, def clauses,
                            when guards, atoms, lists, tuples, case/of, list
                            comprehensions, maps-as-tuples, binaries)
      -> erlang_parser     (build the typed ErlangModule AST: a -module + -export,
                            a -record of 2 fields, two multi-clause guarded
                            functions, a function with a case of 2 clauses, a
                            function with a list comprehension generator+filter)
      -> erlang_to_hir     (lower the ErlangModule to the real HIRModule)
      -> hir_to_erlang     (raise the HIRModule back to an ErlangModule)
      -> erlang_printer    (emit the ErlangModule back to valid Erlang text)
      -> re-lex / re-parse  (re-parse the emitted text into ErlangModule2)
      -> structural + CONTENT equality on the key constructs

The Erlang pipeline uses the typed ErlangModule frontend AST (hir_nodes-backed
HIRModule in the middle). erlang_printer (the file under test) prints the
ErlangModule the backend raises from HIR, so the round-trip drives the printer
on real translated output, then re-parses to prove the printed text is valid
Erlang carrying the original content.

DEPTH: the probe does NOT merely check that nodes exist. On the re-parsed
ErlangModule2 it asserts the CONTENTS survive: the -module name; >= 6 function
names; a multi-clause function (clause count > 1); a `when` guard's presence on
a clause; a -record's 2 field names; a list-comprehension generator + filter;
a case's clause count. A translator that dropped members or a printer that
emitted unparseable text makes this probe FAIL.

Exit code: number of failed assertions (0 == all passed). No exit_with_code.
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/erlang/erlang_lexer.runa" as ErlangLexer
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/erlang/erlang_parser.runa" as ErlangParser
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/erlang/erlang_to_hir.runa" as ErlangFrontend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/erlang/erlang_printer.runa" as ErlangPrinter
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/erlang/hir_to_erlang.runa" as ErlangBackend
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dict
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as TestUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Typed-AST field decoders (read struct fields through Layout offsets)
Note: ============================================================================
Note:
The frontend AST nodes are 8-byte-packed Runa structs. The probe reaches them
through proc list_get / dict get which return raw Integer handles, so struct
fields are read by their byte offset rather than `.field` (the compiler cannot
resolve a typed field on an Integer-typed handle). The offsets mirror the Type
declarations in erlang_parser.runa exactly:

    ErlangModule        : module_name@0, attributes@8, functions@16, records@24, types@32
    ErlangFunction      : name@0, arity@8, clauses@16, line@24
    ErlangFunctionClause: patterns@0, guards@8, body@16, line@24
    ErlangRecord        : name@0, fields@8, line@16
    ErlangRecordField   : name@0, default_value@8, field_type@16, line@24
    ErlangExpression    : expr_type@0, expr_data@8, line@16
:End Note

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Pipeline helpers
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Drives the front-of-pipeline (create lexer -> lex into the parallel token/lexeme/
line arrays -> create parser -> parse) into the typed ErlangModule AST. Both
round-trip rounds (original source and emitted text) run this identical helper so
any structural divergence is attributable to the emitter under test, not to a
difference in how the inputs were driven. The lexer stores its three parallel
arrays into reserved slots at offsets 40/48/56, exactly as erlang_to_hir_from_source
reads them; this helper mirrors that contract.
@End Reasoning
Process called "source_to_module" takes source as Integer returns Integer:
    If source is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let lexer be proc create_erlang_lexer from ErlangLexer with source
    If lexer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc lex_erlang_to_arrays from ErlangFrontend with lexer

    Let tokens_list be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 40
    Let lexemes_list be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 48
    Let lines_list be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 56

    Let parser be proc create_erlang_parser from ErlangParser with tokens_list, lexemes_list, lines_list
    Let erl_module be proc parse_erlang_module from ErlangParser with parser
    Return erl_module
End Process

@Reasoning:
Locates a function in a module's functions list by name. The functions field is a
RunaList of ErlangFunction structs whose name is the first field (offset 0). A
linear scan is robust to function order and count.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_function" takes functions as Integer, want_name as Integer returns Integer:
    If functions is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc list_length from List with functions
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let func be proc list_get from List with functions, index
        If func is not equal to 0:
            Let func_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with func, 0
            Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with func_name, want_name
            If matches is equal to 1:
                Return func
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Finds the first expression of a given expr_type tag inside a function's clause
bodies. Each clause's body is a List of ErlangExpression; the probe scans every
clause body for a node whose expr_type matches the requested kind (e.g. "case",
"list_comprehension", "record_create"). Bounded by clause count and body length,
so it always terminates.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_expr_in_function" takes func as Integer, tag as Integer returns Integer:
    If func is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let clauses be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with func, 16
    Let clause_count be proc list_length from List with clauses
    Let ci be 0
    While ci is less than clause_count:
        Let clause be proc list_get from List with clauses, ci
        If clause is not equal to 0:
            Let body be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with clause, 16
            Let body_count be proc list_length from List with body
            Let bi be 0
            While bi is less than body_count:
                Let stmt be proc list_get from List with body, bi
                If stmt is not equal to 0:
                    Let stmt_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with stmt, 0
                    Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with stmt_type, tag
                    If matches is equal to 1:
                        Return stmt
                    End If
                End If
                Set bi to bi plus 1
            End While
        End If
        Set ci to ci plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns 1 if a record-field list (RunaList of ErlangRecordField) contains a field
whose name matches the target, else 0. Used to assert the -record field name set
survives round-trip. The field name is the first field (offset 0) of each struct.
@End Reasoning
Process called "record_has_field" takes fields as Integer, want_name as Integer returns Integer:
    If fields is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc list_length from List with fields
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let field be proc list_get from List with fields, index
        If field is not equal to 0:
            Let field_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with field, 0
            Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with field_name, want_name
            If matches is equal to 1:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns 1 if a list-comprehension's qualifier list (RunaList of {type,...} dicts)
contains a qualifier whose "type" key equals the target ("generator" or "filter"),
else 0. Proves both the generator (Pat <- List) and the filter survive round-trip.
@End Reasoning
Process called "qualifiers_have_type" takes qualifiers as Integer, want_type as Integer returns Integer:
    If qualifiers is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc list_length from List with qualifiers
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let qual be proc list_get from List with qualifiers, index
        If qual is not equal to 0:
            Let qual_type be proc get from Dict with qual, "type"
            If qual_type is not equal to 0:
                Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with qual_type, want_type
                If matches is equal to 1:
                    Return 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the head-variable name bound by a function clause's first parameter
pattern, or 0 when that pattern is not a plain variable. A clause's patterns
list is at offset 0 (ErlangFunctionClause.patterns); patterns[0] is an
ErlangExpression with expr_type at offset 0 and expr_data at offset 8. For a
variable pattern the expr_data dict carries the bound name under key "name".
Used to prove the emitted clause head binds the original source identifier
rather than a synthetic arg0.
@End Reasoning
Process called "head_var_name" takes clause as Integer returns Integer:
    If clause is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let patterns be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with clause, 0
    If patterns is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pcount be proc list_length from List with patterns
    If pcount is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let head be proc list_get from List with patterns, 0
    If head is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let head_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with head, 0
    Let is_var be proc string_equals from StringCore with head_type, "var"
    If is_var is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let head_data be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with head, 8
    Let name be proc get from Dict with head_data, "name"
    Return name
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns 1 if any expression in a clause's body references a variable whose name
matches want_name, else 0. The clause body is at offset 16; each body element
is an ErlangExpression. A direct top-level var reference (expr_type "var" with
expr_data["name"] == want_name) proves the head binding is actually used by the
body - the unified-binding fidelity check for helper(N) -> N. Bounded by body
length so it always terminates.
@End Reasoning
Process called "body_references_var" takes clause as Integer, want_name as Integer returns Integer:
    If clause is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If want_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let body be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with clause, 16
    If body is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let bcount be proc list_length from List with body
    Let bi be 0
    While bi is less than bcount:
        Let bexpr be proc list_get from List with body, bi
        If bexpr is not equal to 0:
            Let btype be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with bexpr, 0
            Let b_is_var be proc string_equals from StringCore with btype, "var"
            If b_is_var is equal to 1:
                Let bdata be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with bexpr, 8
                Let bname be proc get from Dict with bdata, "name"
                If bname is not equal to 0:
                    Let same be proc string_equals from StringCore with bname, want_name
                    If same is equal to 1:
                        Return 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set bi to bi plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns 1 if a case-clause list contains a clause whose first pattern is the
atom literal want_value (e.g. the atom 'ok'), else 0. Each case clause is an
ErlangFunctionClause whose patterns list (offset 0) holds the match pattern at
index 0; an atom pattern is an ErlangExpression with expr_type "atom" and
expr_data["value"] == want_value. This proves the case clause's literal pattern
survives the round-trip instead of being flattened to the wildcard '_'.
@End Reasoning
Process called "case_clause_has_atom_pattern" takes clauses as Integer, want_value as Integer returns Integer:
    If clauses is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ccount be proc list_length from List with clauses
    Let ci be 0
    While ci is less than ccount:
        Let clause be proc list_get from List with clauses, ci
        If clause is not equal to 0:
            Let patterns be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with clause, 0
            If patterns is not equal to 0:
                Let pcount be proc list_length from List with patterns
                If pcount is greater than 0:
                    Let pat be proc list_get from List with patterns, 0
                    If pat is not equal to 0:
                        Let pat_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pat, 0
                        Let is_atom be proc string_equals from StringCore with pat_type, "atom"
                        If is_atom is equal to 1:
                            Let pat_data be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pat, 8
                            Let pat_value be proc get from Dict with pat_data, "value"
                            If pat_value is not equal to 0:
                                Let same be proc string_equals from StringCore with pat_value, want_value
                                If same is equal to 1:
                                    Return 1
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set ci to ci plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the variable name a comprehension's first generator qualifier binds, or
0 when no generator qualifier carries a variable pattern. A generator qualifier
is a {type:"generator", pattern:..., list:...} dict; its "pattern" is an
ErlangExpression whose expr_type (offset 0) is "var" with expr_data["name"] the
bound variable. This proves the generator's pattern variable survives the
round-trip instead of becoming '_'.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generator_pattern_var_name" takes qualifiers as Integer returns Integer:
    If qualifiers is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc list_length from List with qualifiers
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let qual be proc list_get from List with qualifiers, index
        If qual is not equal to 0:
            Let qual_type be proc get from Dict with qual, "type"
            If qual_type is not equal to 0:
                Let is_gen be proc string_equals from StringCore with qual_type, "generator"
                If is_gen is equal to 1:
                    Let pat be proc get from Dict with qual, "pattern"
                    If pat is not equal to 0:
                        Let pat_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pat, 0
                        Let is_var be proc string_equals from StringCore with pat_type, "var"
                        If is_var is equal to 1:
                            Let pat_data be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pat, 8
                            Let pat_name be proc get from Dict with pat_data, "name"
                            Return pat_name
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Probe entry point
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be proc create_test_results from TestUtils
    proc begin_suite from TestUtils with results, "Erlang translation round-trip"

    Note:
    Representative program exercising the full declaration surface:
    - -module(calc) + -export of 6 functions
    - -record(point, {x, y}) of 2 fields
    - classify/1 : two guarded clauses (when X > 0 / when X < 0) -- multi-clause + guard
    - helper/1   : a single clause returning its argument
    - categorize/1 : a case of 2 pattern clauses
    - squares/0  : a list comprehension with a generator AND a filter
    - make_point/2 : a record creation
    - add/2      : a binary-op body
    :End Note
    Let source be "-module(calc).\n-export([classify/1, helper/1, categorize/1, squares/0, make_point/2, add/2]).\n-record(point, {x, y}).\nclassify(X) when X > 0 ->\n    positive;\nclassify(X) when X < 0 ->\n    negative.\nhelper(N) ->\n    N.\ncategorize(V) ->\n    case V of\n        ok ->\n            good;\n        error ->\n            bad\n    end.\nsquares() ->\n    [X * X || X <- [1, 2, 3, 4], X > 2].\nmake_point(A, B) ->\n    #point{x = A, y = B}.\nadd(A, B) ->\n    A + B.\n"

    Note: --- Stage 0: source -> ErlangModule1 (lex, parse) ---
    Let mod1 be proc source_to_module with source
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "frontend produced ErlangModule", mod1

    Let mod1_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with mod1, 0
    Let mod1_name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with mod1_name, "calc"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "module name is 'calc'", mod1_name_ok, 1

    Let mod1_functions be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with mod1, 16
    Let mod1_fn_count be proc list_length from List with mod1_functions
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "module has at least 6 functions", mod1_fn_count, 6

    Note: --- Stage 1: ErlangModule1 -> HIRModule ---
    Let hir1 be proc translate_erlang_module_to_hir from ErlangFrontend with mod1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "frontend lowered module to HIR", hir1

    Note: --- Stage 2: HIRModule -> ErlangModule (backend raises HIR back to AST) ---
    Let raised be proc generate_erlang_module_from_hir from ErlangBackend with hir1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "backend raised HIR to ErlangModule", raised

    Note: --- Stage 3: ErlangModule -> Erlang text (PRINTER UNDER TEST) ---
    Let config be proc create_emitter_config from ErlangPrinter
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "printer emitter config created", config

    Let emitted be proc emit_module from ErlangPrinter with raised, config
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "printer produced Erlang text", emitted
    Let emitted_len be proc string_length from StringCore with emitted
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "emitted Erlang is non-empty", emitted_len, 0

    Note: --- Stage 4: re-parse the emitted text -> ErlangModule2 ---
    Let mod2 be proc source_to_module with emitted
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "re-parse of emitted Erlang produced ErlangModule2", mod2

    Note: --- Stage 5: CONTENT equality on the key constructs (ErlangModule2) ---

    Note: module name survives
    Let mod2_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with mod2, 0
    Let mod2_name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with mod2_name, "calc"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves module name 'calc'", mod2_name_ok, 1

    Note: function names + count survive (depth, not just existence)
    Let mod2_functions be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with mod2, 16
    Let mod2_fn_count be proc list_length from List with mod2_functions
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves >= 6 functions", mod2_fn_count, 6

    Let classify2 be proc find_function with mod2_functions, "classify"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves function 'classify'", classify2
    Let helper2 be proc find_function with mod2_functions, "helper"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves function 'helper'", helper2
    Let categorize2 be proc find_function with mod2_functions, "categorize"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves function 'categorize'", categorize2
    Let squares2 be proc find_function with mod2_functions, "squares"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves function 'squares'", squares2
    Let make_point2 be proc find_function with mod2_functions, "make_point"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves function 'make_point'", make_point2
    Let add2 be proc find_function with mod2_functions, "add"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves function 'add'", add2

    Note: multi-clause function survives (classify has 2 clauses)
    Let classify2_clauses be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with classify2, 16
    Let classify2_clause_count be proc list_length from List with classify2_clauses
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves classify multi-clause (> 1)", classify2_clause_count, 1

    Note: when-guard survives on classify's first clause
    Let classify2_clause0 be proc list_get from List with classify2_clauses, 0
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip classify clause 0 present", classify2_clause0
    Let classify2_guards be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with classify2_clause0, 8
    Let classify2_guard_count be proc list_length from List with classify2_guards
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves classify 'when' guard", classify2_guard_count, 1

    Note: -record field names survive (point has x and y)
    Let mod2_records be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with mod2, 24
    Let mod2_record_count be proc list_length from List with mod2_records
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves >= 1 record", mod2_record_count, 1
    Let point2 be proc list_get from List with mod2_records, 0
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip record 0 present", point2
    Let point2_fields be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with point2, 8
    Let point2_field_count be proc list_length from List with point2_fields
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves record's 2 fields", point2_field_count, 2
    Let has_x be proc record_has_field with point2_fields, "x"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves record field 'x'", has_x, 1
    Let has_y be proc record_has_field with point2_fields, "y"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves record field 'y'", has_y, 1

    Note: case clause count survives (categorize's case has 2 clauses)
    Let case2 be proc find_expr_in_function with categorize2, "case"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves case node in categorize/1", case2
    Let case2_data be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with case2, 8
    Let case2_clauses be proc get from Dict with case2_data, "clauses"
    Let case2_clause_count be proc list_length from List with case2_clauses
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves case's 2 clauses", case2_clause_count, 2

    Note: list-comprehension generator + filter survive (squares)
    Let lc2 be proc find_expr_in_function with squares2, "list_comprehension"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves list comprehension in squares/0", lc2
    Let lc2_data be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lc2, 8
    Let lc2_qualifiers be proc get from Dict with lc2_data, "qualifiers"
    Let lc2_qual_count be proc list_length from List with lc2_qualifiers
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip comprehension has >= 2 qualifiers", lc2_qual_count, 2
    Let has_generator be proc qualifiers_have_type with lc2_qualifiers, "generator"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves comprehension generator", has_generator, 1
    Let has_filter be proc qualifiers_have_type with lc2_qualifiers, "filter"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves comprehension filter", has_filter, 1

    Note: ============================================================================
    Note: --- Stage 6: FIDELITY assertions (GAP 1 + GAP 2) ---
    Note: ============================================================================
    Note:
    These assertions are stronger than structural existence: they prove the
    emitted Erlang is FAITHFUL, not lossy. They FAIL on the pre-fix behaviour
    (synthetic arg0 heads, and clause/generator patterns flattened to '_') and
    PASS once the source parameter names and clause/generator patterns survive
    the round-trip.
    :End Note

    Note: (a) FIDELITY: a function clause's PARAMETER NAME is the head variable
    Note: AND matches a reference in the body. helper(N) -> N must round-trip as
    Note: a head variable "N" whose name also appears as a "var" reference in the
    Note: clause body - proving the binding is unified (not arg0 with a dangling
    Note: body reference to N). A lossy emitter prints helper(arg0) -> N, leaving
    Note: N unbound; this asserts the head var equals a body var.
    Let helper2_clauses be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with helper2, 16
    Let helper2_clause0 be proc list_get from List with helper2_clauses, 0
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "fidelity helper clause 0 present", helper2_clause0
    Let helper2_head_name be proc head_var_name with helper2_clause0
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "fidelity helper head var present", helper2_head_name
    Let helper2_head_is_n be proc string_equals from StringCore with helper2_head_name, "N"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "fidelity helper head var is source name 'N' (not arg0)", helper2_head_is_n, 1
    Let helper2_body_binds_head be proc body_references_var with helper2_clause0, helper2_head_name
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "fidelity helper body references the head var (binding unified)", helper2_body_binds_head, 1

    Note: (b) FIDELITY: a case clause's PATTERN literal value survives. The
    Note: categorize/1 case has a clause matching the atom 'ok'; on the re-parsed
    Note: HIR2 that clause's pattern must be the atom 'ok', NOT the wildcard '_'.
    Let case2b be proc find_expr_in_function with categorize2, "case"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "fidelity case node present in categorize", case2b
    Let case2b_data be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with case2b, 8
    Let case2b_clauses be proc get from Dict with case2b_data, "clauses"
    Let case2b_has_ok be proc case_clause_has_atom_pattern with case2b_clauses, "ok"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "fidelity case clause pattern 'ok' survives (not '_')", case2b_has_ok, 1

    Note: (c) FIDELITY: a comprehension generator's pattern variable survives.
    Note: squares/0 has [X * X || X <- [...], X > 2]; the generator's pattern is
    Note: the variable X and must round-trip as the var "X", NOT '_'.
    Let lc2c be proc find_expr_in_function with squares2, "list_comprehension"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "fidelity comprehension node present in squares", lc2c
    Let lc2c_data be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lc2c, 8
    Let lc2c_qualifiers be proc get from Dict with lc2c_data, "qualifiers"
    Let lc2c_gen_var be proc generator_pattern_var_name with lc2c_qualifiers
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "fidelity comprehension generator pattern present", lc2c_gen_var
    Let lc2c_gen_is_x be proc string_equals from StringCore with lc2c_gen_var, "X"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "fidelity comprehension generator pattern var 'X' survives (not '_')", lc2c_gen_is_x, 1

    proc print_summary from TestUtils with results
    Let failed be proc get_failed from TestUtils with results
    proc destroy_test_results from TestUtils with results

    Return failed
End Process
